com.esri.mo2.data.gcd
Interface GcdFactory

public interface GcdFactory

Defines an interface for creating and accessing instances of Geocoder, GcdStyle and PropertySequence interfaces.

Method Detail

createGeocoder

public Geocoder createGeocoder(PropertySequence loc_props,
                               String loc_filename)
                        throws GeocoderException
createGeocoder creates an instance of Geocoder with the properties described by loc_props and the name extracted from loc_filename.

Parameters:
loc_props - a property sequence describing geocoder properties.
loc_filename - a string defining the location in which a "locator" (a persistant representation of the geocoder) will be created.
Returns:
an instance of Geocoder.
Throws:
GeocoderException - - if an error has occurred while creating an instance of Geocoder or while creating its persistent representation.

getGeocoder

public Geocoder getGeocoder(String locator_file,
                            String geocode_rule_path)
                     throws GeocoderException,
                            IOException
getGeocoder returns an instance of Geocoder given a string defining a location of a "locator" describing geocoder's properties.

Parameters:
locator_file - a string defining the location of a "locator"
geocode_rule_path - a string defining the location of the geocode rules. If geocode_rule_path is null or empty a default location of geocode rules is used.
Returns:
an instance of Geocoder
Throws:
GeocoderException - - if an error occurs while locating geocode rules.
IOException - - if an error occurs when accessing geocoder properties.

getGcdStyle

public GcdStyle getGcdStyle(String style)
                     throws GeocoderException
getGcdStyle returns an instance of GcdStyle which is a runtime representation of a geocoding style.

Parameters:
style - a name of the geocoding style
Returns:
- a runtime representation of the chosed geocoding style
Throws:
GeocoderException - - if an error occurs when accessing the chosen geocoding style.

getAvailableGcdStyles

public ArrayList getAvailableGcdStyles()
getAvailableGcdStyles returns a Vector of available geocoder style names.

Returns:
- an ArrayList instance with available geocoder style names.

createPropertySequence

createPropertySequence creates an empty instance of PropertySequence

- an instance of PropertySequence
